Hemostatic wrapping of ruptured liver in two postpartum patients.
 A variety of surgical techniques with variable success rates have been reported in the management of the spontaneously ruptured liver in pregnancy.
 We managed two cases of postpartum ruptured liver by wrapping the liver in hemostatic material.
 Hemostatic encapsulation effectively controlled massive bleeding of ruptured livers in two postpartum patients.
